          "date": "2012-09-19 08:44:44.000000000",
          "tz": 240
        },
        "subject": "LU-1071 lnet: add config file support for routes and ip2nets params.",
        "message": "LU-1071 lnet: add config file support for routes and ip2nets params.\n\nLarge network requires many config line for routes, but the module\nparam is limited to 1024 bytes. This patch resolves this limitation.\nThe routes and ip2nets module parameters accept absolute path names,\nthe old syntax is supported as well. Example:\nroutes=\"/etc/lnet_routes.conf\"\n\nSigned-off-by: Alexander Boyko <alexander_boyko@xyratex.com>\nReviewed-by: Alexey Lyashkov <alexey_lyashkow@xyratex.com>\nReviewed-by: Vitaly Fertman <vitaly_fertman@xyratex.com>\nReviewed-by: Isaac Huang <isaac_huang@xyratex.com>\nXyratex-bug-id: MRP-342\nChange-Id: I55be1aa053f001ebe5bfc5613ce7c19231935234\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
